profile_positions.description:
I was the military advisor to the team of human rights officers investigating the human rights violations that occurred during the Sri Lankan civil war. My responsibilities towards the team was to ensure:-
- a correct understanding of the conduct of hostilities, and of the weapons and tactics being used;
- the proper evaluation of the prevailing military situation within which human rights violations occurred;
- a reasonable consideration of the 'military logic'​ which could provide alternate explanations for HR violations;
- adequate preparation for the interviewing of witnesses who had the potential to provide military information.
In addition, my own personal contribution to the enquiry was to provide:-
- the orders of battle of the warring factions, along with profiles of key commanders;
- a narrative describing the evolution of the conflict;
- distinct thematic inputs relating to e.g. indirect fire, the use of surveillance and intelligence & No Fire Zones.
